title: Detectives arrive at Melbourne home of missing mother Karen Ristevski - 9news.com.au
text:
Detectives arrive at Melbourne home of missing mother Karen Ristevski By Sean Davidson Detectives have arrived at the home of missing Melbourne mother Karen Ristevski. 
Detectives from Victoria Police have arrived at the house of missing Melbourne mother Karen Ristevski following the discovery of a woman’s body in Melbourne’s north west yesterday. 
The remains were found by a bushwalker at 12.30pm yesterday, some 25km north from where police in December searched for the missing mother. Karen Ristevski has been missing since June 29. 
Ms Ristevski, who went missing after an argument with her husband at her home, has not been seen for eight months. © Nine Digital Pty Ltd 2017
